snippet.textDisplay:
Great work by Ram Sampath, Sona Mohapatra n Rituraj...
The song "Rangabati" has been improvised so beautifully and most importantly without compromising with the original flavour...

"Vande Utkala Janani" has been one of my all time favourite Oriya songs. And this version of it is as inspiring as the previous ones but with the golden touch of Rituraj's appealing sufi voice.

Loved it!!!

snippet.textDisplay:
This is why Coke Studio India has a bad rep. Khichdi banao janta ko chuna lagao. 

The slight nasal voice was jarring and this version seems like some wannabe cabaret or item song number compared to the original. I wish they'd have picked some female singer from the Odiya music industry instead with a better voice quality + better pronunciation and without the rap segment which just seems forced in the name of fusion and creative freedom to make it sound 'different' why do people touch original classics and folk music if you can't retain the authenticity and feel the need to make so many changes to it. They're just lifting songs and modernising them.
